And listen, if someone comes in your mind right now, pull out your phone, go ahead, and just text them and put Proverbs 17 and 17.

37:35.067 --> 37:38.111
Thank you for being a friend through times of adversity.

37:38.131 --> 37:40.114
Thank you for being a faithful friend because

37:40.354 --> 37:46.040
Sometimes we just need to remember who those faithful friends are and thank God for them.

37:48.002 --> 37:52.346
Ultimately, the best friend you'll ever have is a man named Jesus.

37:54.248 --> 37:58.432
He didn't just come for you and die for you and say, I'm the king, be by servant.

37:58.532 --> 38:03.157
No, he says this to his disciples as he's getting ready to be arrested and crucified.

38:03.177 --> 38:08.402
He says, I no longer call you servants because a servant does not know his master's business.

38:09.058 --> 38:10.600
Instead, I've called you friends.

38:11.341 --> 38:15.448
For everything that I've learned from my father, I have made known to you.

38:17.871 --> 38:19.454
You see the intimacy in this conversation?

38:19.494 --> 38:20.716
You're not just servants.

38:21.236 --> 38:21.817
I'm the king.

38:21.837 --> 38:22.618
You're my servant.

38:23.199 --> 38:26.144
I've let you in on everything my father has told me.

38:26.264 --> 38:27.906
I've drawn you and I trust you.

38:28.688 --> 38:30.771
You are my trusted friend.

38:32.113 --> 38:35.297
You are a friend of the king.

38:36.399 --> 38:38.322
Now, this should blow our minds.

38:39.298 --> 38:45.246
Because how many of you know that you can't always be trusted, that sometimes you say to God, God, I'll serve you, I'll honor you.

38:45.266 --> 38:46.708
