38:52.014 --> 38:52.735
I still love you.

38:53.436 --> 38:55.319
Get back up, try again.

38:55.379 --> 38:56.961
I'm not calling you a servant.

38:57.021 --> 38:58.122
It's not just about obedience.

38:58.162 --> 38:59.344
It's about a relationship.

38:59.364 --> 39:01.587
I call you friends.

39:02.929 --> 39:04.651
I grew up in a church where we sing this song all the time.

39:04.751 --> 39:07.154
What a friend we have in Jesus.

39:08.258 --> 39:10.081
And then it goes through all these things.

39:10.141 --> 39:14.567
This intimate friendship and relationship you can have with the almighty God.

39:14.587 --> 39:15.869
This is what he's after.

39:15.929 --> 39:19.254
And no matter how much you fail, he's always going to be there.

39:19.274 --> 39:24.081
And listen, Jesus had nothing to gain to become your friend.

39:25.022 --> 39:28.988
It's not like Jesus doesn't have to go, man, I really need Doug because without him, we're in trouble.

39:29.829 --> 39:30.970
No, I was a mess.

39:31.050 --> 39:31.711
I was a wreck.

39:31.772 --> 39:34.395
I was in the pit and he pulled me out and said, hey, let's do this together.

39:34.415 --> 39:36.338
I'm like, oh, okay, let's go.

39:37.410 --> 39:40.533
Listen, all of us, if we're really asking, we get in the way of what God wants to do.

39:41.695 --> 39:49.123
But yet he still chooses to use us because there's something about God that loves to work in and through his people.

39:49.203 --> 39:52.126
What a friend we have in Jesus.

39:52.146 --> 39:53.427
Aren't you grateful for Jesus, right?

39:54.989 --> 39:58.333
He had nothing to gain and he's our trusted friend.

39:58.353 --> 40:00.134
Here's the second idea we see in this passage.

40:00.175 --> 40:02.237
Some enemies disguise themselves as friends.

40:04.199 --> 40:07.122
Zippa is undercover, manipulating,

40:08.226 --> 40:10.730
She realized outright just blatantly slandering.

40:12.232 --> 40:14.736
I hit the fells, sort of been quietly rebelling.

40:16.038 --> 40:18.422
You don't always know who your friends and enemies are.

40:18.502 --> 40:20.485
And so how do we respond to that?

40:20.505 --> 40:25.533
Well, the Bible says that we should not be overly, overly naive.

40:26.374 --> 40:30.120
Proverbs 12, 26, a righteous person is cautious in friendship.

40:31.042 --> 40:33.906
Watch people before you entrust yourself to them.

40:34.690 --> 40:36.714
watch their character, watch their behavior.

40:37.035 --> 40:38.878
A righteous person is cautious and friendship.

40:39.159 --> 40:51.864
But we also shouldn't be, again, overly cynical or overly suspicious people and so isolated while the proverb says, if a person falls and they're all by themselves and they have no one to pick them up, you should pick that person.

40:51.904 --> 40:53.708
In the moment of crisis, you have no friends at all.

40:53.728 --> 40:56.754
You don't want to be that person either.

40:58.594 --> 41:01.377
First Corinthians 4 says, judge nothing before the appointed time.

41:01.397 --> 41:07.002
God will bring to light what's hidden and expose the motives of people's hearts.

41:07.023 --> 41:08.344
And so let's process this for a minute.

41:10.326 --> 41:13.709
Have you ever felt the sting of betrayal?

41:18.554 --> 41:26.322
David writes in Psalm 41 that the person I ate bread with, my good friend, he turned on me.

41:28.450 --> 41:35.660
And that sting of knowing someone you were really close to at one time, and then something happens, and you don't even understand it.

41:35.760 --> 41:41.247
It can be so disorienting that you're like, I don't even know how that happened.

41:43.610 --> 41:44.952
And I don't know where to go from here.

41:45.693 --> 41:46.574
Do I trust anyone?

41:46.594 --> 41:48.998
If I can't trust that person, then who can I trust?

41:50.199 --> 41:51.561
And maybe I just don't give up on that friend.

41:51.581 --> 41:53.544
I just give up on friendship altogether, and I just close off.

41:55.646 --> 41:58.290
And one of the things that we want to be conscious of

41:58.978 --> 42:00.379
How do we handle betrayal?

42:00.419 --> 42:03.022
How do we handle a friendship that's close or a family member that's close?

42:03.062 --> 42:05.865
David's dealing with his own son trying to kill him.

42:06.425 --> 42:17.956
I mean, this happens in families, this happens in churches, this happens all the time because human beings are sinful and human beings don't always know how to express what they're thinking and feeling and they have expectations and all these things happening.

42:19.438 --> 42:24.042
How did Jesus respond to betrayal?

42:24.062 --> 42:25.364
Well, two things we see.

42:26.184 --> 42:27.826
One is he didn't retaliate.

42:28.674 --> 42:31.598
He didn't say, if you hurt me, I hurt you back.

42:33.300 --> 42:35.984
Now, he took the humiliation.

42:36.284 --> 42:37.085
He took the betrayal.

42:37.606 --> 42:39.228
He took the insult and said, Father forgive them.

42:40.169 --> 42:40.990
They don't know what they're doing.

42:42.392 --> 42:51.864
But betrayal also didn't make him crumple into despair, or he was in fetal position in the dark all alone saying, I can't believe, I can't believe, I can't believe my life can't go on.

42:51.924 --> 42:56.370
No, he took it because he knew it was in people and he went to the cross

42:57.314 --> 42:59.158
And he died for those sins.

42:59.178 --> 43:05.690
The sins of betrayal that you've experienced and maybe the sins of betrayal that you've orchestrated because all of us have this in us.

43:07.894 --> 43:10.619
Maybe, maybe for you, it's like that.

43:11.942 --> 43:13.385
I think with slander, you ever been slandered?

43:14.547 --> 43:18.234
Oh, your guy named Ziba, I've ever been manipulated by someone using you.

43:18.294 --> 43:20.338
They use you because

43:20.514 --> 43:23.317
With you, I can get to this friend group.

43:23.357 --> 43:24.659
I can get to this place of influence.

43:24.699 --> 43:27.442
With you, I have access to money and resources.

43:27.502 --> 43:29.844
And so there are people who use people like currency.

43:30.165 --> 43:32.487
I'm talking to you because I want something from you.

43:32.648 --> 43:34.349
They're not going to say that out loud, but they're thinking it.

43:35.931 --> 43:40.036
And often, if we're honest, if we look at the Bible as a mirror, there are times that we've done that.

43:40.777 --> 43:45.142
I want to meet with this person because if we have a good meeting, it's going to lead to this and this and this for me.

43:46.423 --> 43:49.106
And the New Testament cautions Christians

43:49.666 --> 43:58.839
Don't be the person who walks toward people for what you can get from them, but walk toward people so that you can serve them.

43:59.640 --> 44:02.584
And this, again, is counter to the way the world thinks.

44:03.666 --> 44:05.248
It's not the way that politics works.

44:05.268 --> 44:06.510
It's not the way the economy works.

44:06.550 --> 44:09.955
It's not the way that social media works, but it's the way the kingdom of God works.

44:09.975 --> 44:11.517
It's the upside down kingdom.

44:13.460 --> 44:17.746
And see, the reality, again, is that

44:19.554 --> 44:29.207
Betrayal and slander and manipulation are the three things that we've all done to God.

44:29.227 --> 44:33.973
Even if you think I've never done that to another person, which you probably have, you've done that to God.

44:36.016 --> 44:38.419
Has anyone ever said, God, I'll never do that again.

44:40.582 --> 44:41.583
I'll never turn my back in here.

44:41.603 --> 44:42.324
I'll always stand for you.

44:42.344 --> 44:49.554
I'll always do this and Tuesday comes and you betray your king.

44:50.946 --> 44:51.406
Slander.

44:57.333 --> 44:58.454
God, I love you, I'll worship you.

44:59.115 --> 45:00.957
But in a rough moment, God, I don't know why you.

45:01.978 --> 45:02.759
Why you didn't do that for me?

45:02.799 --> 45:05.402
And I was talking to my friend, and I don't even know if it's worth following you.

45:05.422 --> 45:12.069
And you're speaking about God in that way, or the church in that way, his bride, or manipulation.

45:12.089 --> 45:15.413
God, I'll do this for you if you do this for me.

45:17.214 --> 45:18.176
Like God's like a vending machine.

45:18.216 --> 45:20.498
If I push this button, I get this, and then I do this for him.

45:21.186 --> 45:24.210
God, if I honor you, then we have this agreement.

45:24.250 --> 45:29.556
You're gonna make sure my business prospers, you're gonna make sure I stay healthy, you're gonna make my kids go good.

45:29.576 --> 45:33.781
And if those don't happen, then I don't know if we're like good.

45:33.821 --> 45:46.035
And the reality is that all of us in some ways do this with God, but aren't you grateful for the grace of Jesus Christ who knew that about us and died for us anyway while we're in our sin?

45:46.055 --> 45:48.658
And that's why we're invited to be a friend of the King.

45:49.922 --> 45:53.947
See, if you're in a moment of crisis in your life right now, here's the last thing we see in this text.

45:53.967 --> 45:59.915
I think this is maybe one of the most encouraging parts of the story that new friendships can emerge in crisis.

46:01.857 --> 46:02.878
Are you in a crisis right now?

46:03.719 --> 46:08.726
And maybe a crisis of relationship in your family, at your job, with your friends?

46:10.207 --> 46:15.474
That may be a gift to allow new friendships to emerge.

46:15.650 --> 46:28.350
When Mary and Joseph were in the middle of a really rough moment and Herod's killing all the babies and then trying to get out, God sends a few friends, the Magi, and they've been gold and frankincense and myrrh to refresh Mary and Joseph in this moment.

46:28.390 --> 46:37.363
David is in a crisis and a guy named Shobi and a guy named McEer and a guy named Marzillie, they come and they refresh David and it's sort of like a surprise.

46:37.383 --> 46:44.274
When David's down, he doesn't realize these guys care for him or love him or would risk anything for him and yet they do.

46:44.546 --> 46:51.515
The Bible says in Proverbs 1824, a man of many companions may come to ruin, but there is a friend who sticks closer than a brother.

46:51.535 --> 46:59.166
If you have a lot of friends, you might not have the friend you need at the moment you need, but sometimes God will surprise you with new friends.

47:02.370 --> 47:08.678
The Apostle Paul, when he became a Christian, well, let's say the day before he became a Christian, he had a lot of friends.

47:10.561 --> 47:12.784
He was like the Pharisee of Pharisees.

47:12.824 --> 47:14.546
He was like the head of the religious leaders.

47:14.978 --> 47:16.480
He was a friend of the Roman government.

47:16.500 --> 47:17.902
He had soldiers following him.

47:18.362 --> 47:19.804
He had access to resources.

47:20.585 --> 47:21.166
He had it all.

47:21.266 --> 47:21.987
He was like the man.

47:23.268 --> 47:28.495
When he met Gias on the road to Damascus, when he was knocked off his high horse, he lost all those friends.

47:29.196 --> 47:31.639
Like in a day, he lost all of them.

47:31.659 --> 47:37.646
And he was sort of stuck because no Christian would talk to him because they thought, oh, this guy was killing Christians on Saturday.

47:37.687 --> 47:39.329
And now on Sunday, he says, he's a Christian.

47:39.349 --> 47:40.210
He's not coming to my house.

47:41.531 --> 47:43.634
So he was canceled by his old friends.

47:44.610 --> 48:01.335
And he was canceled by the church, except for two men, a man named Ananias, who because God spoke to him invites Paul into his house and washes his wounds and washes his eyes and baptizes him and believes him and trusts in him.

48:01.375 --> 48:14.194
And the man named Barnabas, who invites Saul to come and hang out with the disciples and build a new friendship and the apostle Paul becomes the apostle Paul, not just because he met Jesus on the road to Damascus, but because

48:14.466 --> 48:18.913
in a crisis, some new friendships emerge, and that should make us curious.

48:20.535 --> 48:35.900
God, I'm going through this really hard thing in my community, in my group, in my church, in my family, in my friend group, in my job, and maybe as you've revealed some things in people I didn't see, maybe there's a new friend you're bringing into my life.

48:36.400 --> 48:42.610
There's a friend that sticks closer than a brother, and this is why our church is so passionate about you getting connected

48:43.842 --> 48:47.488
Four out of 10 of you are like, I want to develop good and healthy friendships.

48:47.508 --> 48:49.791
Maybe I just don't know how I don't know where the on-ramps are.

48:51.875 --> 49:00.248
Listen, I mean, when I became a Christian, I lost all my friends that I partied with, and I didn't have a lot of new friends that were my age.

49:02.451 --> 49:09.402
And so there's that lonely space in between you when you become a Christian, where you're like, I'm not really the same in this community anymore.

49:09.422 --> 49:11.826
I don't know where my new community is, and if you're

49:11.970 --> 49:18.040
praying, God help me to develop healthy friendships so I can grow in the community of the church.

49:18.100 --> 49:21.265
Then God can provide that if you're looking for it and praying for it.

49:21.285 --> 49:24.229
This is the best place to find those friendships.

49:24.249 --> 49:25.011
I'm not saying you won't get hurt.

49:26.433 --> 49:28.997
I'm only saying this is the best place for that healthy expression to go.

49:29.037 --> 49:37.330
Right now my wife is in El Salvador and she's sending me all these pictures of like 12 different women who were there and they're doing this Calvary women outreach and they're

49:37.442 --> 49:42.207
passing out like gifts to all these children in this community and they're doing church services and they're sharing the gospel.

49:42.227 --> 49:46.853
And you see the joy on the faces of these women who say, we're gonna take a couple of days a week out of our life.

49:46.873 --> 49:47.954
We're gonna travel to another country.

49:47.974 --> 49:51.738
We're gonna go in this great adventure with Jesus and their hearts are being bound together.

49:51.758 --> 49:59.106
They're gonna be friends for life because they stepped out into a new place, into a new moment and watch God work in their life.

49:59.146 --> 50:02.110
And again, this is our heart for you as a church.

50:02.130 --> 50:03.191
This is God's heart for you.

50:04.312 --> 50:06.034
And so in this moment of David's life,

50:07.554 --> 50:10.458
We see these friends and enemies emerge.

50:11.919 --> 50:35.889
And I pray that, again, like David, as a follower of the king, that he is your first and chief friend, but that you also develop these beautiful, healthy friendships by taking risks, not by being naive, but by being cautious and watchful and careful in God in that process can put you in this powerful, beautiful community for the rest of your life.

50:35.909 --> 50:36.530
Can we thank

50:36.866 --> 50:42.392
God for the way that He does this work in the middle of these difficult moments, and let's take a moment and pray.

50:44.194 --> 50:48.998
Father, we pray for everyone in this room that you would help us to find those faithful friends.

50:49.979 --> 50:58.228
That you would help us to work through those issues that maybe separate us, unresolved conflict, unstated expectation.

50:58.909 --> 51:00.751
Sometimes we don't have the courage to talk about it.

51:02.012 --> 51:04.114
We just talk to others about it and it gets worse.

51:05.090 --> 51:13.458
God help us to take down our barriers and allow our hearts to be open, and as we trust you, that you would do something beautiful.

51:15.760 --> 51:23.167
And now I pray, if there's anyone in this room that doesn't know your love, I pray that you would draw them by your grace.

51:23.187 --> 51:27.412
And I pray this in Jesus' name.

51:27.432 --> 51:30.475
Hey, before I say amen, I wanna offer a simple invitation.

51:32.036 --> 51:34.098
You could be a friend of the king,

51:35.138 --> 51:37.281
This is the image of we see of Itai.

51:37.401 --> 51:39.163
This is the image we see of Hushai.

51:39.183 --> 51:40.605
This is the image we see of Abishai.

51:40.685 --> 51:45.050
All these guys that are decided to be friends of the King because at some point in their life, they did this.

51:45.070 --> 51:46.352
They did this.

51:47.313 --> 51:50.437
I pledge my allegiance and my loyalty to you, you are my King.

51:52.359 --> 51:54.662
And well, there's a greater King than David.

51:54.682 --> 51:55.403
His name is Jesus.

51:57.285 --> 51:59.027
David couldn't save people from their sins.

51:59.067 --> 52:04.754
In fact, David let a lot of people down in his life, but Jesus came to be a greater David, a greater King.

52:05.506 --> 52:19.007
He saw you that you were an enemy of God and he came in to this space to live in the dust, to live in the dirt, to breathe air, to experience all of the frustration and pain and futility that the world could bring.

52:19.068 --> 52:26.319
And to be our mediator between us and God, to rebuild the bridge that was broken by our sin.

52:27.741 --> 52:30.706
And then as one of his final acts, he died on the cross.

52:32.322 --> 52:33.844
It didn't allow people to arrest him.

52:33.925 --> 52:34.846
He gave up his life.

52:35.227 --> 52:39.413
This was part of his mission, part of his plan to die in our place, a king who dies for his servants.

52:39.433 --> 52:39.954
Who's heard of that?

52:41.396 --> 52:42.718
This love, so great.

52:44.101 --> 52:46.284
He laid down his life for people who were cursing at him.

52:47.326 --> 52:48.227
And he said, father, forgive them.

52:48.247 --> 52:49.008
They didn't know what they're doing.

52:49.890 --> 52:51.172
And we have to do something with that.

52:51.933 --> 52:57.682
When we see the king of the universe, the one who created all of us dying on a cross for us, we have to decide

52:58.722 --> 52:59.944
Do I think that's nice?

52:59.964 --> 53:00.905
That's for somebody else?

53:00.925 --> 53:02.667
Or do I say, that's the king I want to follow?

53:02.727 --> 53:03.709
So I'm going to bow my knee.

53:04.970 --> 53:08.215
I'm going to confess that my sin is the one who brought him there and put him there.

53:09.236 --> 53:12.581
I'm going to confess that I've lived my life, allegiance to myself.

53:12.641 --> 53:14.744
I'm doing what I want, what I think, what I feel.

53:14.764 --> 53:18.689
But now I want to say, Jesus, if you would do that for me, then there's nothing I wouldn't do for you.

53:18.749 --> 53:23.235
So I admit I need to save you.

53:25.638 --> 53:28.242
And I put my faith in trusting you.

53:29.410 --> 53:32.294
So whatever happens next, it's not what I want to do.

53:33.676 --> 53:35.119
It's what you want to do.

53:35.139 --> 53:36.641
And the Bible calls that repentance.

53:36.701 --> 53:39.205
I change the way I think about my life and who's in charge.

53:39.245 --> 53:44.673
And if you've never done that, I want to invite you to do that today because here's what's at stake.

53:45.875 --> 53:48.038
One day you're going to die and you're going to stand before God.

53:49.661 --> 53:55.730
And the only person who gets into heaven is the person who has no sin on their account.

53:57.282 --> 53:58.985
God doesn't say, well, you did more good than bad.

53:59.025 --> 54:00.447
So yeah, you can come in.

54:01.810 --> 54:04.073
Not everyone goes to heaven.

54:04.093 --> 54:06.517
In fact, because of our sin, hell is our default destination.

54:06.557 --> 54:10.965
The only people to get into heaven are the ones that say, I'm a friend of the king.

54:10.985 --> 54:12.788
I'm with him.

54:14.210 --> 54:20.741
And because he died on the cross and because I received his forgiveness, I have no debt to pay.

54:20.761 --> 54:23.666
My debt has been paid in full.

54:24.898 --> 54:30.247
And that requires a decision, an act of your will to say, I don't just pray when I'm in trouble.

54:31.048 --> 54:32.631
I don't just pray to thank God for my food.

54:33.432 --> 54:37.919
I don't just go to church because it makes me feel better about the way that I've had guilt in my life for the week.

54:37.939 --> 54:39.101
So I stamp it, I feel good.

54:39.121 --> 54:44.670
Now, this is a relationship with the living God, a relationship with the king where you can say, I'm a friend of the king, it's my identity.

54:45.351 --> 54:47.074
It gives me my sense of purpose.

54:47.094 --> 54:48.536
And you've been surrounded, right?

54:48.576 --> 54:50.700
You're surrounded by people who have made that decision.

54:50.740 --> 54:52.082
We are not perfect people.

54:53.186 --> 54:55.429
but we are forgiven people, people who belong to the king.

54:56.289 --> 54:58.492
And so here's how we give you an opportunity to make that decision.

54:58.532 --> 55:11.226
We play a closing song and say, if you want to start a relationship with God through his son, Jesus, if you're ready to repent of your sins and give your life over to God, if you're ready to bow your knee and say, I'm gonna give my allegiance to one person, his name is Jesus.

55:12.047 --> 55:16.172
Then we're gonna ask you to stand up from wherever you are as this song is being played and walked forward.

55:16.612 --> 55:18.034
And we're gonna lead you in a very simple prayer.

55:18.054 --> 55:21.778
And we're gonna celebrate with all of heaven as you come, if that's you.

55:21.922 --> 55:23.945
Stand now and walk this way.

55:23.986 --> 55:40.534
We have been praying for you and we can't wait to see what he's going to do in your life.

55:40.554 --> 55:40.754
Come down.

56:33.026 --> 56:38.053
There's still time to come if you're still in your seats because this is going to be a moment you don't want to miss.

56:38.073 --> 56:38.654
Listen, we are.

56:40.417 --> 56:43.361
We're clapping right now because we know what this means.

56:43.421 --> 56:45.724
We know what it meant for us as you pray this prayer.

56:47.547 --> 56:50.832
The Bible says every sin you've ever committed is going to be washed away, wiped away.

56:51.352 --> 56:58.002
As far as the east is from the west, God separates that from you and all the blame and all the shame and all the stuff.

56:59.202 --> 57:04.911
And as he writes your name in this book, called The Book of Life, and as he fills you with his spirit, he's going to begin to do the work of new creation.

57:06.033 --> 57:10.059
And he's going to take some of that mess, some of that unresolved stuff, and he's going to turn into something beautiful.

57:10.079 --> 57:12.002
He's going to make it a message because he's the Redeemer.

57:12.022 --> 57:12.743
This is what he does.

57:14.646 --> 57:18.392
And so you're about to say the most powerful words that will ever come out of your mouth for your entire life.

57:19.594 --> 57:24.722
Because the Bible says, by your confession, that you confess Jesus is King, Jesus is Lord.

57:25.698 --> 57:29.803
and you believe in your heart that God are raising you that the Bible says you will be saved.

57:31.404 --> 57:34.268
And so if your hearts are ready, God's listening.

57:35.209 --> 57:37.011
And he's been waiting for this moment your entire life.

57:38.192 --> 57:39.814
Say this to God.

57:39.834 --> 57:44.759
Lord God, I open my heart and I invite you inside.

57:46.021 --> 57:46.902
Forgive my sin.

57:48.003 --> 57:49.424
Today I repent.

57:50.906 --> 57:54.450
Now fill me with your spirit and I will walk with you.

57:55.042 --> 57:56.065
all the days of my life.

57:56.928 --> 57:59.916
I pray this in Jesus name.

57:59.936 --> 58:00.919
Amen.

58:00.939 --> 58:01.601
Amen, guys.

58:01.621 --> 58:02.564
Congratulations.

58:03.286 --> 58:04.670
Welcome to the family of God.

58:05.372 --> 58:08.722
So before you go back to your seats, I want to ask you for five minutes.

58:08.962 --> 58:10.544
You just made that most important decision.

58:10.565 --> 58:11.686
I want to meet you personally.

58:11.706 --> 58:13.048
I want to give you a Bible as a gift.

58:13.109 --> 58:14.330
You'll be back with your friends in a moment.

58:14.350 --> 58:16.193
So follow this crew over here to the open door.

58:16.213 --> 58:16.834
I'll meet you there.

58:17.095 --> 58:18.217
Be back with your friends in a moment.

58:18.257 --> 58:26.770
Church, let's give them a hand as they go and let's stand and close in a song of worship to our King Jesus who is worthy of our praise.

01:00:12.674 --> 01:00:14.858
Thanks for listening to today's message.

01:00:14.898 --> 01:00:18.323
Here at Calvary, we believe a relationship with Jesus changes everything.

01:00:18.944 --> 01:00:26.156
And if you've decided to follow Jesus, we'd love for you to text the word believe to 31352, so you can find out what it means to follow Christ.

01:00:26.937 --> 01:00:32.146
And to learn more about Calvary and all of our campuses, you're free to visit calvaryftl.org.

